Build a complete Next.js 15 website for VaultVerified, a B2B security platform that prevents Business Email Compromise (BEC) fraud. Follow these exact requirements:

BUSINESS CONTEXT:
VaultVerified eliminates payment fraud by removing banking changes from email systems entirely. Core philosophy: "Email should never be a system of record for money." Target audience: Finance teams, AP teams, Security leaders at enterprise organizations.

DESIGN REQUIREMENTS:

Inspired by Bank of America's clean, organized, accessible design (https://www.bankofamerica.com/deposits/checking/advantage-banking/)

Clean, calm, authoritative feel - NOT futuristic or AI-looking

Enterprise-grade appearance with minimal scrolling per page

Professional color scheme suitable for financial services

Responsive design with mobile-first approach

Reference design: https://divide-quest-43186657.figma.site

SITE ARCHITECTURE:

Navigation:
- Home
- Solutions (dropdown)
  - Vault (Secure Banking Updates)
  - NACHA Compliance & Audit  
  - VAAS (Outsourced Verification)
- Resources
- Company
- Contact

Persistent CTAs: "Request a Demo" + "Sign Up"

Copy
PAGE STRUCTURE & CONTENT:

1. HOME PAGE:

Hero: "Secure payment changes. Verified identity. Built-in compliance."

Subtext: "VaultVerified prevents ACH and wire fraud by removing banking changes from email, verifying real identities, and creating an auditable, compliant verification process."

Section 2: "Fraud doesn't start with a bad actor - it starts with a trusted email" (educational content about BEC)

Section 3: "Email was never meant to be a financial system" (core problem)

Section 4: Three solution cards (Vault, NACHA, VAAS)

2. SOLUTIONS PAGES:

Vault: 5 W's structure (What/Who/Why/Where/When)

NACHA: March 2026 compliance changes, requirements, how VaultVerified meets standards

VAAS: Verification-as-a-Service description, what's handled, benefits

3. SUPPORTING PAGES:

Resources: Blog, articles, case studies, guides

Company: Mission, philosophy

Contact: Form, support, demo requests

TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:

Next.js 15 with App Router

TypeScript throughout

Tailwind CSS for styling

Responsive design

SEO optimized

Fast loading performance

Accessibility compliant

TONE & MESSAGING:

Calm, authoritative, structured

Educational approach (not fear-based)

No hype or fear tactics

Enterprise-grade credibility

Focus on prevention over reaction

KEY DIFFERENTIATORS TO HIGHLIGHT:

Prevention over reaction

Identity over intent

Process over policy

Trust through verification

Compliance built-in, not bolted-on

Create a complete, production-ready website that positions VaultVerified as the authoritative solution for enterprise payment fraud prevention, with clean Bank of America-inspired design and comprehensive content covering all specified sections.


